list.item:
—lay our your views on European security matters, in particular our
                        policies on the CSCE and Mutual and
                        Balanced Force Reductions (MBFR);

div.p:
In addition to these issues, Kreisky may want to:
—discuss his efforts to give Austria a more dynamic intermediary role in East-West relations;
—explain Austriaʼs vital interest in negotiating an industrial free trade area with the European Community and seek your support for these negotiations.

list.item:
—indicate that we see improvement of relations with Moscow as
                                    a protracted process and point out the areas of difference that
                                    persist;

—explain that at present we see more advantages to the Soviets
                                    than to the West in a European Conference or in any broad effort
                                    to devise an all-European security system;

—explain that Austria wants a link with an enlarged EC as a whole to counterbalance
                                    growing German economic influence in Austria, which raises
                                    Soviet suspicions;

—say that we recognize that Austria, because of the State
                                    Treaty, cannot become a full EC
                                    member and we consider it a special case;

—express sympathy for Austriaʼs need to reach some arrangement
                                    with the EC short of full
                                    membership;

item.p:
If this comes up, you should restate our Near Eastern position, with which the Austrians may not be fully familiar. You should say that:
—work on this crucial issue should not be postponed until the convening of a Conference, whose date is indefinite;
—the parties directly involved should negotiate settlement;
—the best avenue for progress lies in the “proximity talks” between Israel and Egypt, which we are ready to help arrange, on an interim agreement to reopen the Suez Canal.
